  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Constructivism purposes a learner-centered approach which promotes critical thinking, problem-solving, and meaningful engagement in the learning process (Bruner, 1996).",
    "Since constructivism requires active participation of learners in the learning process, the teacher's role is facilitator rather than a lecturer (Ebo, 2018).",
    "The lesson plans in constructivism, thus, suggest settings to have students construct their knowledge and understanding (Darchinian et al., 2021).",
    "The lesson plan should provide inquiry-based learning, group activities, reflection, scaffolding and real-world connections (Vu, 2019).",
    "Then, learners' confidence in their ability to succeed in the learning task plays a crucial role in their motivation."
  ],
